# Theme and Design Guidance

This project already centralizes shared visual language in `src/theme`.

## Source of Truth

Use these files before creating new visual tokens:

- `src/theme/colors.ts`
- `src/theme/typography.ts`
- `src/theme/appBrand.ts`
- `src/theme/strings.ts`
- related background and vibe files in `src/theme/`

## Rules

- Reuse existing theme tokens first.
- Add new shared colors or typography tokens in `src/theme` instead of scattering them through feature files.
- Keep brand naming aligned with `src/theme/appBrand.ts`.
- Keep user-facing copy aligned with `src/theme/strings.ts` where applicable.
- Preserve the app's immersive background-driven visual style when adding screens.

## When to Add a Token

Add a shared token when:

- the same value appears in multiple screens
- the value reflects brand or system meaning
- the token improves consistency across features

Keep a local inline value only when it is clearly one-off and not part of the shared design language.
